kind.prompt:
You are implementing a university course catalog Blazor Web App. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-cbbd83d452ae4b00b7d33215d5c0901e/UniversityCourseCatalog` using `dotnet new blazor -int Server` (per-page Interactive Server).

## Requirements
- Browse departments and courses in a searchable, filterable list
- View course detail pages (description, schedule, credits, instructor bio)
- Students submit an enrollment request form (name, student ID, course selection) — standard HTML form, no wizards or real-time validation
- Homepage shows featured courses and department links
- No authentication
- Intranet with fast connectivity

## Architecture decisions
- **Static SSR** for: Homepage, Course Detail, Enrollment Form (standard HTML POST form with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]`)
- **Interactive Server** for: Course Catalog page (needs live search/filter without page reloads)
- Use an in-memory data service (no database) with sample data for departments, courses, instructors
- Keep Bootstrap for styling (already included in template)

## Implementation Tasks

### 1. Create Data Models (`Models/` folder)
Create `/tmp/sv-cbbd83d452ae4b00b7d33215d5c0901e/UniversityCourseCatalog/Models/` with:

**Department.cs:**
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Department
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Code { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

**Course.cs:**
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Course
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Title { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Code { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Description { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public int Credits { get; set; }
    public string Schedule { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public int DepartmentId { get; set; }
    public string DepartmentName { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public Instructor Instructor { get; set; } = new();
    public bool IsFeatured { get; set; }
}
```

**Instructor.cs:**
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Instructor
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Email { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Bio { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Office { get; set; } = string.Empty;
}
```

**EnrollmentRequest.cs:**
```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class EnrollmentRequest
{
    [Required(ErrorMessage = "Name is required.")]
    [StringLength(100)]
    public string StudentName { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required(ErrorMessage = "Student ID is required.")]
    [RegularExpression(@"^[A-Z]{2}\d{6}$", ErrorMessage = "Student ID must be 2 uppercase letters followed by 6 digits (e.g., CS123456).")]
    public string StudentId { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Required(ErrorMessage = "Please select a course.")]
    [Range(1, int.MaxValue, ErrorMessage = "Please select a course.")]
    public int CourseId { get; set; }
}
```

### 2. Create Data Service (`Services/` folder)

**Services/ICatalogService.cs:**
```csharp
using UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Services;

public interface ICatalogService
{
    List<Department> GetDepartments();
    Department? GetDepartment(int id);
    List<Course> GetCourses();
    List<Course> GetFeaturedCourses();
    List<Course> GetCoursesByDepartment(int departmentId);
    Course? GetCourse(int id);
    List<Course> SearchCourses(string? searchTerm, int? departmentId);
    bool SubmitEnrollmentRequest(EnrollmentRequest request);
}
```

**Services/CatalogService.cs:** — Implement with rich sample data. Include at least 4 departments (Computer Science, Mathematics, Physics, English) with 3-4 courses each. Each course should have a realistic instructor with a bio. Mark 3-4 courses as featured.

### 3. Register the Service in Program.cs

Add `builder.Services.AddSingleton<ICatalogService, CatalogService>();` and add `using UniversityCourseCatalog.Services;`.

### 4. Update Navigation (`Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor`)

Replace the counter and weather nav items with:
- Home (href="")
- Course Catalog (href="courses")
- Departments (href="departments")
- Enroll (href="enroll")

Update the brand name to "University Course Catalog".

### 5. Update Layout (`Components/Layout/MainLayout.razor`)

Replace the "About" link in the top-row with "University Intranet — Course Catalog" text.

### 6. Create Pages

**Delete** `Counter.razor` and `Weather.razor`.

**Components/Pages/Home.razor** — Static SSR page:
- Hero section with welcome message
- "Featured Courses" section showing featured courses as Bootstrap cards (title, code, credits, department, link to detail)
- "Departments" section with links to filter courses by department

**Components/Pages/Courses.razor** — Interactive Server page (`@rendermode InteractiveServer`):
- Search input (text box for filtering by title/code)
- Department dropdown filter
- Results displayed as a table or card list
- Each course links to its detail page
- Real-time filtering as user types (no submit button needed)

**Components/Pages/CourseDetail.razor** — Static SSR page with route `@page "/courses/{Id:int}"`:
- Course title, code, credits
- Full description
- Schedule information
- Instructor name, email, office, bio
- Link back to courses list
- Link to enroll in this course

**Components/Pages/Departments.razor** — Static SSR page:
- List all departments with descriptions
- Each department links to courses filtered by that department

**Components/Pages/Enroll.razor** — Static SSR page with HTML form:
- Use `EditForm` with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]` and `FormName`
- Fields: Student Name, Student ID, Course (dropdown of all courses)
- DataAnnotationsValidator for validation
- On successful submission, show a confirmation message
- Include `<AntiforgeryToken />` if using plain `<form>`, or use `<EditForm>` which handles it automatically

### 7. Update `_Imports.razor`

Add:
```
@using UniversityCourseCatalog.Models
@using UniversityCourseCatalog.Services
```

### 8. Build Verification

After all files are created, run `dotnet build` in the project directory and fix any errors.

## Important Notes
- Do NOT set `@rendermode` on pages that don't need interactivity (Home, CourseDetail, Departments, Enroll)
- The Enroll page uses standard SSR form handling with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]` — no `@rendermode` needed
- Only the Courses page (with live search/filter) gets `@rendermode InteractiveServer`
- Use `@inject ICatalogService CatalogService` to access data
- For the Enroll form, after successful POST show a success message on the same page

